added.title: BL4Z3
added.description: The Titans become hackers to stop a gang of computer pirates.

added.title: Career Day
added.description: Robin forces the other Titans to forget their dreams and find regular, boring jobs.

added.title: Two Parter Part 1
added.description: The Titans visit the Hall of Justice to use the pool, but then decide to check out the inside.

added.title: Two Parter Part 2
added.description: The Titans must save the members of the Justice League from the clutches of the supervillain Darkseid.

added.title: Blaze
added.description: Los Titanes se convierten en hackers para detener a una pandilla de piratas informáticos.

added.title: Dia de los Trabajos
added.description: Robin obliga a los demás Titanes a olvidar sus sueños y a conseguir trabajos normales y aburridos.

added.title: Esto llega hasta el Once
added.description: Durante una última parada en una juguetería antes del viaje inaugural de Ben, Gwen y el Abuelo Max a través del Atlántico, Ben se encuentra con su antiguo bravucón, Kevin 11, que ahora tiene nuevos poderes. Es capaz de transformarse en alienígenas al igual que Ben, como el doble "pirata" de Cannonbolt: iWreckingbolt!

added.title: Truth
added.description: An old Plumber partner of Max's resurfaces with nefarious intentions and ends up stealing the dangerous Null Void Projector.

added.title: Framed
added.description: Kevin 11 is back and out for revenge. And with the ability to shape-shift into several of Ben's alien heroes, he's been framing Ben for his crimes.

added.title: Tough Luck
added.description: Gwen's Lucky Girl powers return when she buys a magical stone at a magic convention in Las Vegas. However, Hex is after the same stone, and after his niece breaks him out of prison, the two set off to retrieve the stone.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 2
added.description: Ben and Rook discover an underground city beneath Bellwood populated with aliens! But who is terrorizing them? (Introducing Nemetrix alien BugLizard, & Ben alien Shocksquatch, Psyphon, Fistina, Bubblehelmet, Liam.)

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: Malefactor
added.description: Khyber and his dog attacks Ben and Rook while they're at the "Olde Bellwood Days" festival, but does the hunter have other plans? (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Hypnotick.)

added.title: Once Upon a Townsville
added.description: When a dainty princess on a mission comes to Townsville, the girls must learn the superhero way isn't always the right way.

added.title: Store 23
added.description: While out looking for the elusive 23rd Mr. Smoothy's store with Blukic and Driba, Ben meets an alternate version of himself. (Guest-starring Aziz Ansari as Ben 23.)

removed.title: Skips Stress
removed.description: Skips has to lower his stress before it kills him.

removed.title: The Dome Experiment
removed.description: Benson wants to prove that he was right about the date of the Dome Experiment.

removed.title: Treasure Map
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang don't have money to pay for their meal at a restaurant.  But when they discover a treasure map, it could be the answer to all their problems.  Too bad the treasure map is actually a restaurant activity placemat.

removed.title: BBBDay!
removed.description: It's Beast Boy's birthday! But will the other Titans remember?

removed.title: Locked Out
removed.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets locked out of his RV and accidentally sets off the security system, it's up to him and his friends to disarm it before it destroys them.

removed.title: Nickname
removed.description: When a kid wants a cool nickname, UG tells him he has to earn it in the most legendary way ever: yard work!

removed.title: BBCYFSHIPBDAY
removed.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg celebrate the birthday of their friendship.

removed.title: BBSFBDAY!
removed.description: Beast Boy agrees to share his birthday with Starfire after learning she's never had one on Earth.

removed.title: The Ultimate Heist
removed.description: Albedo seeks a device that will finally change him back into his Galvan form; meanwhile, Ben is locked in Plumber HQ prison.

removed.title: The Avogodo
removed.description: It's Cinco de Mayo and Robin learns that avocados are a super food that give you super powers.

removed.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
removed.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

removed.title: Cough It Up
removed.description: Psyphon and a gang of bounty hunters are after Argit, who is in possession of a dangerous weapon!

removed.title: Weapon XI Part 1
removed.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

removed.title: Paint Job
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to paint a house.

removed.title: The Frogs of War Part 2
removed.description: With Ben missing, the Incurseans now control the Earth. It's up to Rook and the remaining Plumbers to lead the resistance and fight back! (Introducing new Ben alien, Bullfrag.)

removed.title: Brilliant Century Duck Crisis Special
removed.description: The park guys want to get rid of a very large bird in the park.

removed.title: A Change of Face
removed.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

removed.title: Driver's Test
removed.description: When a girl has trouble passing her driving test, Uncle Grandpa shows up to help her.  But when they accidentally set a Crazy Baby loose in the city, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to stop it... by teaching the girl how to drive!

removed.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 1
removed.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

removed.title: Blue Ribbon Blues
removed.description: When a famous scientist comes to the school, Blossom will stop at nothing to impress him at the Science Fair even if that means putting Townsville in danger!

removed.title: Midnight Madness
removed.description: When the Rustbucket breaks down outside the largest mall in the U.S., it seems Ben and Gwen will have the time of their lives in the mall. That is until they run into an evil hypnotist entertaining the crowd, who puts Ben under hypnosis, causing him to sleepwalk at night and help him steal things. And when the hypnotist discovers certain aliens are now helping him, he exploits them for his grand plan of hypnotizing hundreds of people so they'll be under his demented control forever. Ben must figure out how to break the spell he's under and stop this evil plan.

removed.title: Uncle Grandpa Ate My Homework
removed.description: When Uncle Grandpa shows up and mistakenly eats a kid's Egyptian diorama for school, he helps the kid bring an actual pyramid to class, but accidentally unleashes an evil mummy on the world.

removed.title: Stick Hockey
removed.description: After Benson unjustifiably throws out Mordecai and Rigby's stick hockey table, he feels guilty and tries to help them get it back.
